```{r}
library(tidyverse)
mpg

```


```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))
```
# 3.2.4 Exercises
```{r}
#1.Run ggplot(data = mpg). What do you see?
ggplot(data = mpg)
#I see a blank plot

#2.How many rows are in mpg? How many columns?

dim(mpg)
# has 234 rows and 11 columns.

#3.What does the drv variable describe?
#describes the type of drivetrain

#4.Make a scatterplot of hwy vs cyl.
ggplot(data = mpg, aes(x = cyl, y = hwy)) +
  geom_point()

#5. What happens if you make a scatterplot of class vs drv? Why is it not useful?
ggplot(data = mpg, aes(x = class, y = drv)) +
  geom_point()
#not useful because both variables are categorical.

```

```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color = class))
```

```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, size = class))

```

```{r}
# Left
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, alpha = class))

# Right
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, shape = class))
```

```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy), color = "blue")
```

```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_wrap(~ class, nrow = 2)
```

```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_grid(drv ~ cyl)
```
```{r}
#1) What happens if you facet on a continuous variable?
#get one panel per unique value—usually tons of panels with 0–1 points ,it is  not useful.
```

